    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">In-Depth Performance</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Image Quality & 1-Inch Sensor</h3>
        <p>
          The jump to a 1-inch sensor transforms the Pocket 3 into a legitimate video tool. Low-light footage that would be unusable on phones or action cameras looks clean and professional here. The larger sensor captures approximately 2.5 stops more light than the Pocket 2, dramatically reducing noise in indoor and evening situations.
        </p>
        <p>
          Color science is excellentâ€”skin tones are natural and pleasing straight out of camera. D-Log M provides 10-bit footage with approximately 10 stops of dynamic range for color grading. The f/2.0 aperture and 20mm equivalent field of view are ideal for vlogging and content creation. 4K 120p slow motion is sharp and detailed, though at a slight crop.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Gimbal Stabilization</h3>
        <p>
          The 3-axis mechanical gimbal delivers stabilization that electronic systems cannot match. Walking footage is buttery smooth, panning is precise and controlled, and there's no rolling shutter warping. The gimbal motors are whisper-quietâ€”inaudible in recordings even with the built-in microphones.
        </p>
        <p>
          ActiveTrack 6.0 provides exceptional subject trackingâ€”the gimbal physically follows your subject while maintaining smooth, professional movements. Face tracking is remarkably sticky, keeping creators in frame during movement. The gimbal's range of motion handles most shooting scenarios, though extreme angles may require repositioning. The startup time of approximately 2 seconds (flip the screen, shoot) is unmatched.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Audio & Connectivity</h3>
        <p>
          Built-in stereo microphones are surprisingly capable for a device this smallâ€”audio quality exceeds most action cameras. Wind noise can be an issue outdoors, mitigated by the included wind cover. The real magic happens with DJI Mic 2 integration: wireless audio without a receiver, appearing as a clean track in recordings.
        </p>
        <p>
          The 2.0" rotating touchscreen (700 nits brightness) enables instant switching between horizontal and vertical contentâ€”physically rotating the camera's orientation. The screen is readable in direct sunlight. USB-C connectivity enables fast charging (50% in 15 minutes) and direct webcam usage. Built-in WiFi and Bluetooth enable smartphone control via the DJI Mimo app.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Form Factor & Practicality</h3>
        <p>
          At 179 grams, the Pocket 3 truly fits in a pocketâ€”something no stabilized camera has achieved before with a 1-inch sensor. The ergonomic handle provides a secure grip during one-handed operation. The magnetic mount system enables quick attachment to various accessories (tripods, extension rods, mounts).
        </p>
        <p>
          Battery life of approximately 166 minutes (1080p 24fps) is respectable. The non-removable battery is a limitation for all-day shootingâ€”pack a USB-C power bank or the optional battery handle. Build quality is solid but not ruggedized: the Pocket 3 is not waterproof or shockproof without accessories. Treat it as premium electronics, not an action camera.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="affiliate">
